# 🛠️ Advanced Virtual Cybersecurity Homelab

## 📋 Project Overview
This repository documents the end-to-end design, deployment, configuration, and maintenance of an isolated virtual security testing environment. The purpose of this homelab is to provide a safe, controlled sandbox to analyze network data flows, observe how web protocols transmit information, and understand the structural mechanics of both secure and insecure network services.

By building this infrastructure from scratch, I am applying core principles of **Network Defense (Blue Teaming)**, systems engineering, and virtualization management.

---

## 🗺️ Network Architecture & Topology

To maintain complete safety and prevent experimental traffic from leaking onto the physical home network or the public internet, the environment is strictly contained within an isolated **Layer 2 broadcast domain** using Oracle VirtualBox.

| Device Name | Operating System | Role / Function | Network Interface Mode | Assigned IP Address |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Analysis Workstation** | Kali Linux (2026.1) | Traffic monitoring, auditing, and log analysis | Host-Only Adapter | `192.168.100.249` |
| **Target Server** | Metasploitable 2 | Hosting legacy web services (HTTP, FTP, SSH) | Host-Only Adapter | *[Pending Verification]* |
| **Virtual Switch** | VirtualBox Engine | Handles local frame switching (Subnet `192.168.100.0/24`) | Internal DHCP Disabled | Local Broadcast Only |

