## 🚀 Active Learning Objectives & Lab Milestones

Once the network layer is fully stabilized, this repository will document the technical output of the following defensive labs:

### 🔬 Lab 1: Interface Verification & Connectivity Testing
* **Objective:** Establish clear end-to-end communication channels.
* **Command Verification:** Execute mutual ICMP verification requests (`ping -c 4 <destination_ip>`) to confirm the path is clear.
* **Documentation:** Capture terminal logs proving successful network handshakes.

### 🔬 Lab 2: Plaintext Protocol Analysis (HTTP POST Extraction)
* **Objective:** Analyze how unencrypted forms pass authentication tokens across a local area network.
* **Methodology:** Launch **Wireshark** on interface `eth0`, filter for `http`, navigate to the local web application port (`http://192.168.100.X`), and observe how a login request packages fields into raw text.
* **Blue Team Takeaway:** Documenting the precise visibility of cleartext traffic highlights the business necessity for modern TLS/SSL encryption ($HTTPS$).

